      • expectedExceptionType

        public PrivateConstructorTester.Builder expectedExceptionType​(java.lang.Class<? extends java.lang.Throwable> expectedType,
                                                              java.lang.String expectedMessage)
        Sets the expected type of exception and message that must be thrown by the constructor of required class. If you don't want to check exception message, you can set just type of the exception.
        Parameters:
        expectedType - type of the exception that must be thrown by the constructor of required class, should not be null.
        expectedMessage - message of the exception that must be thrown by the constructor of required class, can be null.
        Returns:
        ExceptionCheckAble.
